<h2 id="_general_information">1. General information</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The online service <strong>bit.ly</strong> gives you the possibility of shortening long URLs on its website. If you saved a valid configuration for the URL shortening service, bit.ly, then the URLs that plentymarkets automatically generates for tweets on <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/extras/twitter">Twitter</a> (chapter 4) will be directly shortened.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_registration">2. Registration</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you don’t have a bit.ly account yet, then go to the website and <a href="https://bitly.com/a/sign_in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sign up</a>&nbsp;<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-external-link  "></i></span>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_configuration">3. Configuration</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as follows to set up bit.ly in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up bit.ly:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Client » Settings » Services » bit.ly</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter your user name under <strong>Login</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the API key that you received from bit.ly under <strong>API key</strong>.<br>
→ If you are logged into bit.ly, then you will find the API key <a href="http://bit.ly/a/your_api_key" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>&nbsp;<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-external-link  "></i></span>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
